pokemon.name: chikorita
pokemon.text_entry: In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

pokemon.name: bayleef
pokemon.text_entry: Bayleef’s neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

pokemon.name: meganium
pokemon.text_entry: The fragrance of Meganium’s flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe’s fighting spirit.

pokemon.name: cyndaquil
pokemon.text_entry: Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

pokemon.name: quilava
pokemon.text_entry: Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

pokemon.name: typhlosion
pokemon.text_entry: Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

pokemon.name: totodile
pokemon.text_entry: Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile’s jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

pokemon.name: croconaw
pokemon.text_entry: Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

pokemon.name: feraligatr
pokemon.text_entry: Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

pokemon.name: sentret
pokemon.text_entry: When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

pokemon.name: furret
pokemon.text_entry: Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

pokemon.name: hoothoot
pokemon.text_entry: It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some Trainers use them in place of clocks.

pokemon.name: noctowl
pokemon.text_entry: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.

pokemon.name: ledyba
pokemon.text_entry: These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.

pokemon.name: ledian
pokemon.text_entry: It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.

pokemon.name: spinarak
pokemon.text_entry: Although the poison from its fangs isn’t that strong, it’s potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

pokemon.name: ariados
pokemon.text_entry: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.

pokemon.name: crobat
pokemon.text_entry: It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokémon. If it can’t drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.

pokemon.name: chinchou
pokemon.text_entry: On the dark ocean floor, its only means of communication is its constantly flashing lights.

pokemon.name: lanturn
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

pokemon.name: pichu
pokemon.text_entry: The electric sacs in its cheeks are small. If even a little electricity leaks, it becomes shocked.

pokemon.name: cleffa
pokemon.text_entry: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

pokemon.name: igglybuff
pokemon.text_entry: Taking advantage of the softness of its body, Igglybuff moves as if bouncing. Its body turns a deep pink when its temperature rises.

pokemon.name: togepi
pokemon.text_entry: It is considered to be a symbol of good luck. Its shell is said to be filled with happiness.

pokemon.name: togetic
pokemon.text_entry: It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.

pokemon.name: natu
pokemon.text_entry: Because its wings aren’t yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

pokemon.name: xatu
pokemon.text_entry: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

pokemon.name: mareep
pokemon.text_entry: Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You’ll want to pet it because it’s cute, but if you use your bare hand, you’ll get a painful shock.

pokemon.name: flaaffy
pokemon.text_entry: It stores electricity in its fluffy fleece. If it stores up too much, it will start to go bald in those patches.

pokemon.name: ampharos
pokemon.text_entry: Its tail shines bright and strong. It has been prized since long ago as a beacon for sailors.

pokemon.name: bellossom
pokemon.text_entry: Bellossom gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

pokemon.name: marill
pokemon.text_entry: Even after Marill swims in a cold sea, its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That’s why this Pokémon is never cold.

pokemon.name: azumarill
pokemon.text_entry: These Pokémon create air-filled bubbles. When Azurill play in rivers, Azumarill will cover them with these bubbles.

pokemon.name: sudowoodo
pokemon.text_entry: It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining.

pokemon.name: politoed
pokemon.text_entry: The cry of a male is louder than that of a female. Male Politoed with deep, menacing voices find more popularity with the opposite gender.

pokemon.name: hoppip
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

pokemon.name: skiploom
pokemon.text_entry: Skiploom’s flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

pokemon.name: jumpluff
pokemon.text_entry: Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

pokemon.name: aipom
pokemon.text_entry: It searches for prey from the tops of trees. When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet, Aipom gets excited and pounces.

pokemon.name: sunkern
pokemon.text_entry: Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

pokemon.name: sunflora
pokemon.text_entry: Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

pokemon.name: yanma
pokemon.text_entry: Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

pokemon.name: wooper
pokemon.text_entry: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

pokemon.name: quagsire
pokemon.text_entry: Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.

pokemon.name: espeon
pokemon.text_entry: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.

pokemon.name: umbreon
pokemon.text_entry: On the night of a full moon, or when it gets excited, the ring patterns on its body glow yellow.

pokemon.name: murkrow
pokemon.text_entry: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow’s presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.

pokemon.name: slowking
pokemon.text_entry: Slowking can solve any problem presented to it, but no one can understand a thing Slowking says.

pokemon.name: misdreavus
pokemon.text_entry: What makes it happy is imitating the voices of weeping people and scaring everyone. It doesn’t deal well with folks who aren’t easily frightened.

pokemon.name: unown
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

pokemon.name: wobbuffet
pokemon.text_entry: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

pokemon.name: girafarig
pokemon.text_entry: Girafarig’s rear head contains a tiny brain that is too small for thinking. However, the rear head doesn’t need to sleep, so it can keep watch over its surroundings 24 hours a day.

pokemon.name: pineco
pokemon.text_entry: It sticks tree bark to itself with its saliva, making itself thicker and larger. Elderly Pineco are ridiculously huge.

pokemon.name: forretress
pokemon.text_entry: In the moment that it gulps down its prey, the inside of its shell is exposed, but to this day, no one has ever seen that sight.

pokemon.name: dunsparce
pokemon.text_entry: The nests Dunsparce live in are mazes of tunnels. They never get lost in their own nests—they can tell where they are by the scent of the dirt.

pokemon.name: gligar
pokemon.text_entry: Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

pokemon.name: steelix
pokemon.text_entry: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

pokemon.name: snubbull
pokemon.text_entry: In contrast to its appearance, it’s quite timid. When playing with other puppy Pokémon, it sometimes gets bullied.

pokemon.name: granbull
pokemon.text_entry: Although it’s popular with young people, Granbull is timid and sensitive, so it’s totally incompetent as a watchdog.

pokemon.name: qwilfish
pokemon.text_entry: The small spikes covering its body developed from scales. They inject a toxin that causes fainting.

pokemon.name: scizor
pokemon.text_entry: Though its body is slim, Scizor has tremendous attacking power. Even Scizor’s muscles are made of metal.

pokemon.name: shuckle
pokemon.text_entry: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

pokemon.name: heracross
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon takes pride in its strength, which allows it to lift things 100 times heavier than itself with no trouble at all.

pokemon.name: sneasel
pokemon.text_entry: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.

pokemon.name: teddiursa
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

pokemon.name: ursaring
pokemon.text_entry: In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

pokemon.name: slugma
pokemon.text_entry: Slugma does not have any blood in its body. Instead, intensely hot magma circulates throughout this Pokémon’s body, carrying essential nutrients and oxygen to its organs.

pokemon.name: magcargo
pokemon.text_entry: Magcargo’s body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Water is vaporized on contact. If this Pokémon is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

pokemon.name: swinub
pokemon.text_entry: If it smells something enticing, it dashes off headlong to find the source of the aroma.

pokemon.name: piloswine
pokemon.text_entry: Although its legs are short, its rugged hooves prevent it from slipping, even on icy ground.

pokemon.name: corsola
pokemon.text_entry: These Pokémon live in warm seas. In prehistoric times, many lived in the oceans around the Galar region as well.

pokemon.name: remoraid
pokemon.text_entry: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine’s underside to scavenge for leftovers.

pokemon.name: octillery
pokemon.text_entry: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

pokemon.name: delibird
pokemon.text_entry: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon, so it’s always scrounging around for more food.

pokemon.name: mantine
pokemon.text_entry: As it majestically swims, it doesn’t care if Remoraid attach to it to scavenge for its leftovers.

pokemon.name: skarmory
pokemon.text_entry: People fashion swords from Skarmory’s shed feathers, so this Pokémon is a popular element in heraldic designs.

pokemon.name: houndour
pokemon.text_entry: They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.

pokemon.name: houndoom
pokemon.text_entry: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

pokemon.name: kingdra
pokemon.text_entry: Scales shed by this Pokémon have such a splendorous gleam to them that they’ve been given to royalty as gifts.

pokemon.name: phanpy
pokemon.text_entry: Phanpy uses its long nose to shower itself. When others gather around, they thoroughly douse each other with water. These Pokémon can be seen drying their soaking-wet bodies at the edge of water.

pokemon.name: donphan
pokemon.text_entry: If Donphan were to tackle with its hard body, even a house could be destroyed. Using its massive strength, the Pokémon helps clear rock and mud slides that block mountain trails.

pokemon.name: porygon2
pokemon.text_entry: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2, the Pokémon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.

pokemon.name: stantler
pokemon.text_entry: Stantler’s magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

pokemon.name: smeargle
pokemon.text_entry: It draws symbols with the fluid that oozes from the tip of its tail. Depending on the symbol, Smeargle fanatics will pay big money for them.

pokemon.name: tyrogue
pokemon.text_entry: Even though it is small, it can’t be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

pokemon.name: hitmontop
pokemon.text_entry: After doing a handstand to throw off the opponent’s timing, it presents its fancy kick moves.

pokemon.name: smoochum
pokemon.text_entry: Highly perceptive sensors, Smoochum’s lips are kept moist by its daily application of tree sap.

pokemon.name: elekid
pokemon.text_entry: When its horns shine a bluish white, that’s the sign it’s fully charged. You’ll get a shocking jolt if you touch it!

pokemon.name: magby
pokemon.text_entry: Its body temperature is always around 1,100 degrees Fahrenheit. If Magby falls into a small- enough pond, the whole thing will dry up.

pokemon.name: miltank
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon needs to be milked every day, or else it will fall ill. The flavor of Miltank milk changes with the seasons.

pokemon.name: blissey
pokemon.text_entry: Blissey lays mysterious eggs that are filled with happiness. It’s said that anyone who eats a Blissey egg will start acting kindly to all others.

pokemon.name: raikou
pokemon.text_entry: Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

pokemon.name: entei
pokemon.text_entry: Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

pokemon.name: suicune
pokemon.text_entry: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

pokemon.name: larvitar
pokemon.text_entry: It feeds on soil. After it has eaten a large mountain, it will fall asleep so it can grow.

pokemon.name: pupitar
pokemon.text_entry: It will not stay still, even while it’s a pupa. It already has arms and legs under its solid shell.

pokemon.name: tyranitar
pokemon.text_entry: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

pokemon.name: lugia
pokemon.text_entry: Lugia’s wings pack devastating power—a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

pokemon.name: ho-oh
pokemon.text_entry: Ho-Oh’s feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

pokemon.name: celebi
pokemon.text_entry: This Pokémon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength, and it can heal wounds, too.
